# Project core

Desktop-first Vite/React/TS POC. Prefer the existing layering; do not invent parallel math or lesson pipelines.

## Layers (keep boundaries)

| Layer | Path | Rule |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Pure math | `src/math/` | No React, no Mafs, no Motion Canvas. Production must not import `mathjs` (`mathjs` is devDependency only). |
| Shared examples | `src/math/examples.ts`, `src/lessons/exampleData.ts` | Guided + explorers share example ids — never duplicate matrix/vector constants. |
| Guided | `src/guided-scenes/` | Lessons pass `guidedSceneId` only; React never imports Motion Canvas scene modules directly. |
| Explorations | `src/explorations/` | Register in `registry.tsx`; reuse `MafsSceneShell`, controls, toggles, readouts. |
| Lessons / UI | `src/lessons/`, `src/components/lesson/` | Registry-driven; no per-lesson branching in the shell. |

## Scope

- Lessons 1–2 + M4.5 polish are the active product surface.
- Do **not** implement Lessons 3–4 / determinants / eigenvectors milestones unless the user explicitly reopens that work.
- Prefer fixing visual/math correctness and shared helpers over new lesson content.

## Math & copy

- Learner-facing math uses KaTeX (`ProseWithMath`, equation/readout components) — including MC choices when they are matrices/vectors.
- Prefer `matrixVectorMultiply` / shared helpers over ad-hoc formulas in UI code.

## Correctness docs

Before changing math or visualizations: `docs/MATH_CORRECTNESS.md`, `docs/ERROR_LOG.md`. Checklist: `docs/LESSON_CORRECTNESS_CHECKLIST.md`.

## Verify

After meaningful changes: `npm run lint`, `npm run test`, and e2e when touching player/layout/lesson flow (`npm run test:e2e`).
